1. Database Philosophy

The database is designed around four principles.

1. Single Source of Truth

Master data (Districts, Blocks, Police Stations, etc.) is stored only once.

Questions reference master records instead of duplicating text.

2. AI Ready

Every question should be traceable through the complete AI lifecycle.

Submission

↓

Translation

↓

Normalization

↓

Embedding

↓

Cluster

↓

Canonical Question

↓

Report

3. Analytics Optimized

The schema should support:

Dashboard analytics
District analytics
Weekly reports
Department reports
Trend analysis

without excessive joins.

4. Soft Delete

Citizen submissions remain for

90 Days

↓

Automatic deletion

↓

Aggregated analytics remain permanently.

