13. INDEX STRATEGY

Indexes on:

district_id
department_id
scheme_id
created_at
language
ai_processing_status
report_type

Composite indexes:

(district_id, created_at)

(department_id, created_at)

(language, created_at)

(report_type, generated_at)

GIN indexes:

normalized_question (PostgreSQL full-text search)
JSONB fields (if introduced later)
14. PARTITION STRATEGY

The question_submissions table will become the largest table.

Partition by month based on created_at.

Example:

question_submissions_2026_01
question_submissions_2026_02
question_submissions_2026_03

Benefits:

Faster queries
Faster retention cleanup
Better maintenance
15. DATA RETENTION POLICY
Data	Retention
Raw question submissions	90 days
AI clusters	Permanent
Canonical questions	Permanent
Generated reports	Permanent
Audit logs	7 years
Email delivery logs	1 year
AI processing logs	180 days
Redis cache	24 hours
Queue jobs	7 days
16. Database Optimizations
UUID primary keys throughout
Foreign key constraints on all relationships
Soft deletes for citizen data
Monthly partitioning of submissions
Read replicas supported for analytics
Qdrant used for vectors instead of storing embeddings in PostgreSQL
Redis used exclusively for ephemeral data (sessions, queues, cache)